#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:3
msgid "Transformations"
msgstr "変形"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:5
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "リファレンス"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:14
msgid ""
"Transform menu in Object Mode. The yellow highlighted sections are only "
"available in Object Mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:17
msgid ""
"Transformations refer to a number of operations that can be performed on a "
"selected Object or Mesh that alters its position or characteristics. Basic "
"transformations include grabbing (moving), rotating or scaling a selection. "
"More advanced transformations included mirroring, giving the selection "
"sphere like qualities, shear, push/pulling and warping. The following links "
"provide a more detailed explanation of the more available transformation "
"operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:25
msgid "Basic transformations"
msgstr "基本的な変形"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:27
msgid ""
":doc:`Grab/Move </3d_interaction/transformations/basics/grab>`: move a "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:28
msgid ""
":doc:`Rotate </3d_interaction/transformations/basics/rotate>`: rotate a "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:29
msgid ""
":doc:`Scale </3d_interaction/transformations/basics/scale>`: change the size"
" of a selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:33
msgid "Advanced Transformations"
msgstr "高度な変形"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:35
msgid ""
":doc:`Mirror </3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/mirror>`: mirror the "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:36
msgid ""
":doc:`To Sphere </3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/to_sphere>`: make "
"the selection have a more spherical shape."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:37
msgid ""
":doc:`Shear </3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/shear>`: shear the "
"selection. Shearing causes parallel selections to move past one another."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:38
msgid ""
":doc:`Warp </3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/warp>`: warp the "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:39
msgid ""
":doc:`Shrink/Fatten "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/shrink_fatten>`: Move vertices "
"along their normals (Mesh Editmode only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:40
msgid ""
":doc:`Push/Pull </3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/push_pull>`: push "
"or pull the selection (imagine someone pushing or pulling at the ends of the"
" selection to stretch or compress it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:41
msgid ""
":doc:`Move Texture Space "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/move_texture_space>`: Texture "
"space determines the placement of textures. Moving it can be useful when "
":doc:`mapping textures. </textures/mapping>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:42
msgid ""
":doc:`Scale Texture Space "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/scale_texture_space>`: As above. "
"Useful when :doc:`mapping textures. </textures/mapping>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:43
msgid ""
":doc:`Align to Transform Orientation "
"</3d_interaction/transform_control/transform_orientations>`: Aligns the "
"Object to the current Transform Orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:44
msgid ""
":doc:`Geometry to Origin </modeling/objects#object_centers>`: Move the "
"Object's geometry to the origin point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:45
msgid ""
":doc:`Origin to Geometry </modeling/objects#object_centers>`: Move the "
"Object's origin to its geometry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:46
msgid ""
":doc:`Origin to 3D cursor </modeling/objects#object_centers>`: Move the "
"Object's origin to the 3D cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:47
msgid ""
":doc:`Randomize Transform "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/randomize_transform>`: Apply "
"random movement, rotation and scale to selected Objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:48
msgid ""
":doc:`Align Objects "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/align_objects>`: Align Objects "
"along a particular axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:49
msgid ""
":doc:`Animated Transforms to Deltas "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/advanced/animated_transforms_to_deltas>`: "
"Converts animated Transform values to Delta Transform values. Allows "
"duplicated Objects with keyframes to have offsets (location, rotation, scale"
" etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:53
msgid "Transform Control"
msgstr "変形のコントロール"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:55
msgid ""
"In addition to the specific controls on each of the above pages, there are a"
" number of general controls that can be used to modify the effects of the "
"listed transformations. This includes using keyboard input for precise "
"control, resetting transformations and axis locking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transformations.rst:60
msgid ""
":doc:`Read more about Transform Controls » "
"</3d_interaction/transform_control>`"
msgstr ""
